My absolute favorite go to spot for authentic jamaican oxtails and cuisine! I'm here so regular that I don't even have to order! I just shoe up and pay! Dig it, they got actual love for the culture and it shows in their food! The atmosphere and ambiance is very inviting! Absolutely check them out! And they practice social distance here! 👊🏿

We arrived at this spot for lunch. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we had an excellent feeling. The food was just great. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Keep it up.
I absolutely love this place.  Definitely a top 3 for Caribbean eateries in the DMV.  I highly recommend.
The food is AMAZING!! Reminds me of my Mom's cooking. Definitely recommend this restaurant. Good vibe, great service and amazing entrees.

This spot is my favored. I eat in plenty of restaurants but to this one I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very friendly and the cooking they offer is so yummy. I would always prefer to have a nice dinner in this restaurant. Highly recommended.

Holy cow, the jerk chicken was spectacular! Get that and the oxtail!!

Anyone who enjoys the food here has clearly never had authentic Caribbean food. It lack flavor. I got the jerk chicken and it was so bland, as well as the cabbage.I also got a chicken patty-- VERY DRY! In the middle of the night I had terrible stomach ache and all the food i ate came back up! I would not recommend.
The lady at the front desk couldn’t have been nicer & the oxtail & jerk chicken was bombbb. Definitely recommend!
They are so slow , I waited so long for my food . Every time I asked they put minutes on it but was never honest enough to let me know how long it actually was gonna take .

Never will order from here again in use a credit card i brought food from here using a credit card in the next day i got a notification that someone order doordash using my card in brought almost $40 worth of food and tip the driver 20 i know who is was to but its kool hope golden chi was good to the person who used my card from here.
Come on island time. Believe the hype.

We decided to try Karibbean Kitchen since we're still under quarantine and too lazy to cook.  LOL.  Let's just say I should have cooked.  The chicken was extremely rubbery.  It's not authentic jerk; they just pour a sauce over it.  The collard greens have zero seasoning.  I think they're from a can.  The mac and cheese is dry, also with zero seasoning.  We will not be ordering from here again and I suggest you try someplace else.
The jerk is good
Bless the cook!
Great food service was ok

When I tried to open the door, it was locked even though on the website it said it was open from 4-11PM. It was 6:30PM when I came in. Then a man came up to me and asked "What do you want?" and I said "Food" to which he responded very rudely with "Obviously".  He lets me and my partner in and tells us off hand what he has. We tried asking for a menu and he said "You don't need to see it." We ended up leaving without getting anything and the guy followed us outside and locked the door behind us.  I've never had such a terrible experience at a restaurant before and I didn't even eat there.  It's a shame because I really like Caribbean food, but I will never go here again.

This was a far way from where we were staying in DC, but it was worth the drive.  I enjoyed the jerk chicken, the sauce they used on it, and that it actually tasted jerk!  It is a nice, spacious restaurant and bar, but I did not see adequate parking.  Good vibes once in the house, too with real Jamaican vibes and music!
Delicious, only complaint would be that the cabbage has other vegetables in it and I like my cabbage without all the extras...

Sunday brunch you gotta do it.... Authentic Jamaican food, classy place for happy hour, professional staff all are very warm and smiling,  the prices are wonderful. I will always be a dedicated patron.
Their patties, coco bread and jerk sauce is a constant go-to for quick and tasty food. Love having this place in the neighborhood.
Don't bother ordering from here because after you have paid and already waited over an hour for the food, they cancel your order. This has happened more than once. Terrible.
So good my best spot to go to
Great atmosphere and staff. The food is ridiculously good.

Food tasted good but I waited 45 minutes for my meal.
The food is so flavorful and delicious

Went their to get some oxtails, unfortunately they were out! The cashier recommended jerk chicken instead. OMG!! Not only was the potions of food was worth the price the food was outstanding and delicious. The wait time was not long and the cashier asked if I wanted to take a look around since it was my first time their. Customer service and food food is a plus for me. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone who likes Caribbean food, drinks, and entertainment!!
Went here while in DC with the kids, food was sooo good I had to send wifey a pic back home🤣!
Meh. Tropical punch is good, but the food is subpar. The owner could be more enthusiastic to his patrons, but has a bad attitude that makes coming back a far cry. I might order take out if desperate.

I was so disappointed with the food from this restaurant.  I ordered the oxtail dinner with extra gravy and a side of plantains. The collard greens tasted so nasty.  I’m not accustomed to oxtails with potatoes, so I didn’t like their oxtail dinner either.  There oxtails dinner comes with plantains although it’s not written as such on their Uber Eats menu.  So don’t buy an extra helping on the side because again the dinner comes with it.  Their customer service was good.  It’s just so disappointing that their Jamaican cuisine taste so nasty.  It taste nothing like true Jamaican food.  Such a waste....
Food and service was awesome, looking forward to going back to eat there again 👌🏿💪🏿
The food was absolutely delicious

Good food!!

Food was amazing, my drink was on point. Excellent customer service.

Just left! Great low key spot! Wonderful customer service! Affordable happy hour. Also I enjoyed my curry chicken rice and peas and cabbage! I’m glad I live in the area! Definitely will be coming back.

New spot better get there great environment

I like the food but you guys really need to update your hours of business . I came three days out of the week and all three days you weren't open on time  and it was 2 in the afternoon . The sign says you open at 12 . Well i have only been once when your open at twelve and that was the first time . This is really annoying because you never know when you will be open . I walk all the way from my job to see the door is locked .Please update the times so that i could enjoy the greatness of Karibbean Kitchen
nice ambiance, intimate. Service was a little slower for food than I'd like. Food was okay, flavors were watered down a little for my taste.
Nice an clean good food to eat i do enjoyed almost avery meal i add there wesome

Went to this place one Sunday and they were closed without a sign on the door. Wish there was notice on the website or somewhere about the closing so that I would not have gone out of my way to go there. I came back the following week and ordered to-go. The food was good. I got oxtail, mac&cheese and cabbage. I would not get oxtail again (didn't get much meat) but I will definitely go back.

I just received my order thru UberEats. Let me start by saying, the manager was SOOOOOOOOOOO RUDE!!!!!! I was flabbergasted!!!! I have NEVER in my 44 years had a manager talk to me like she did. I contacted the restaurant to let them know that whoever made the tray didn't put my brownstewed chicken on the tray, and only about three table spoons of rice and plantains. So this ignorant woman had the nerve to hang up on me, then I called backband she said, LOOK WHAT THE HELL YOU WANT ME TO DO?" I was stuck because I was in shock. SERIOUSLY. HOWEVER, I must take some accountability. Because the reviews were not the greatest. Never again.
It's a great Jamaican restaurant where you get all this Caribbean food not spicy just have a lot of Caribbean seasoning means it's off the hook
Jerk chicken!!!!  Visited when first opened and great portions delicious authentic jamaican food! Will be back
Food is great but customer service is always subpar. Please hire different people to handle phone orders.
Big portions with amazing taste

I’m really impress with how comfortable and relaxing on how the atmosphere is at Karibbean Kitchen. I was helped with a gentle hostess Lady who's attitude was surprisingly  pleasant  and charming. My meal was the Jerk Chicken with fries, just a delicious way to start the early morning. Couldn't finish my meal because of how favorable, tasty, as well as how tender the meat. Almost falls off the bone, plus the Goat Meat Meal, just breathtaking. Once you keep your meal in a stable condition you'll begin to smile. And last but not least, the jerk shrimp and chicken. Has just enough rice, beans, tomato and salad it's a favorite. The reason why I say that, so many of the audience explain how beautiful it is. Please wash it down with there homemade sarry tea. I got a great deal for a few meals, June 2,2019/12:10am.

This restaurant has some of the best Jamaican food I’ve had in the area.  They can still work on their timing (sometimes you have to wait more than you expect), but is always worth it.  Their oxtail, curry goat, and jerk chicken are the best! They’re service is always friendly and you’ll find the owner with a big smile to greet you every time.  I live in the community, and I’ve seen them getting involved in different actions (they collaborated for the block party last fall and gave free meals to the neighbors, for example.  I really hope they remain in the area.
The mac 'n cheese is ooey gooey and the Collard Greens are delicious!
While the food was good (or fine depending on who you ask), the service has a lot of room for improvement.
The food is sooo good.

I am so upset that I did not take a picture of the food but I guess I was just so excited to eat it. The food was fantastic. Tasted fresh and authentic. I’m not a pro with Jamaican food and this was my first time really eating it, but I feel like I know good food. And this was good food. Must try it and I will definitely go back.  If you’re in a rush, the food comes out a little slow so take your time and enjoy the time with the staff and other customers. Great vibes in there and from what we heard yesterday, they will be having an upstairs and a patio for summer time fun. I will definitely be going back.
Everything is Great there!!!!!!
The best food !
One of the best Jamacian spots. I highly recommend. Very flavorful and nice staff!
